math/countif.name: COUNTIF
math/countif.shortSummary: Counts cells in a range that satisfy a single criterion.

math/countifs.name: COUNTIFS
math/countifs.shortSummary: Counts cells that satisfy all supplied criteria pairs.

math/csc.name: CSC
math/csc.shortSummary: Returns the cosecant of an angle, defined as `1 / SIN(angle)`.

math/csch.name: CSCH
math/csch.shortSummary: Returns the hyperbolic cosecant of a number, defined as `1 / SINH(x)`.

math/degrees.name: DEGREES
math/degrees.shortSummary: Converts an angle from radians to degrees.

math/even.name: EVEN
math/even.shortSummary: Rounds a number away from zero to the nearest even integer.

math/exp.name: EXP
math/exp.shortSummary: Returns Euler's number `e` raised to the given power.

math/fact.name: FACT
math/fact.shortSummary: Returns the factorial of a non-negative integer.

math/floor.name: FLOOR
math/floor.shortSummary: Rounds a number down to the nearest multiple of a significance.

math/floor-math.name: FLOOR.MATH
math/floor-math.shortSummary: Rounds a number down to the nearest integer or multiple using `FLOOR.MATH` rules.

math/gcd.name: GCD
math/gcd.shortSummary: Returns the greatest common divisor of one or more integers.

math/int.name: INT
math/int.shortSummary: Rounds a number down to the nearest integer.

math/lcm.name: LCM
math/lcm.shortSummary: Returns the least common multiple of one or more integers.

math/ln.name: LN
math/ln.shortSummary: Returns the natural logarithm of a positive number.

math/log.name: LOG
math/log.shortSummary: Returns the logarithm of a number for a specified base.

math/log10.name: LOG10
math/log10.shortSummary: Returns the base-10 logarithm of a positive number.

math/max.name: MAX
math/max.shortSummary: Returns the largest numeric value from one or more arguments.

math/min.name: MIN
math/min.shortSummary: Returns the smallest numeric value from one or more arguments.

math/mod.name: MOD
math/mod.shortSummary: Returns the remainder after division, with the sign of the divisor.

math/mround.name: MROUND
math/mround.shortSummary: Rounds a number to the nearest multiple.

math/multinomial.name: MULTINOMIAL
math/multinomial.shortSummary: Returns the multinomial coefficient for one or more values.

math/odd.name: ODD
math/odd.shortSummary: Rounds a number away from zero to the nearest odd integer.

math/permut.name: PERMUT
math/permut.shortSummary: Returns the number of permutations for selecting and ordering `k` items from `n`.

math/power.name: POWER
math/power.shortSummary: Raises a base number to a specified power.

math/quotient.name: QUOTIENT
math/quotient.shortSummary: Returns the integer portion of a division result, truncated toward zero.

math/radians.name: RADIANS
math/radians.shortSummary: Converts an angle from degrees to radians.

math/roman.name: ROMAN
math/roman.shortSummary: Converts an Arabic number to a Roman numeral string.

math/round.name: ROUND
math/round.shortSummary: Rounds a number to a specified number of digits.

math/rounddown.name: ROUNDDOWN
math/rounddown.shortSummary: Rounds a number toward zero to a specified number of digits.

math/roundup.name: ROUNDUP
math/roundup.shortSummary: Rounds a number away from zero to a specified number of digits.

math/sec.name: SEC
math/sec.shortSummary: Returns the secant of an angle, defined as `1 / COS(angle)`.

math/sech.name: SECH
math/sech.shortSummary: Returns the hyperbolic secant of a number, defined as `1 / COSH(x)`.

math/seriessum.name: SERIESSUM
math/seriessum.shortSummary: Evaluates a power series from coefficients, start power, and step.
math/seriessum.signature: SERIESSUM(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar, arg4: any@scalar)

math/sign.name: SIGN
math/sign.shortSummary: Returns the sign of a number as -1, 0, or 1.

math/sin.name: SIN
math/sin.shortSummary: Returns the sine of an angle in radians.

math/sinh.name: SINH
math/sinh.shortSummary: Returns the hyperbolic sine of a number.

math/sqrt.name: SQRT
math/sqrt.shortSummary: Returns the positive square root of a number.

math/sqrtpi.name: SQRTPI
math/sqrtpi.shortSummary: Returns the square root of a number multiplied by pi.

math/sum.name: SUM
math/sum.shortSummary: Adds numeric values across scalars and ranges.

math/sumif.name: SUMIF
math/sumif.shortSummary: Adds values that satisfy a single criterion.

math/sumifs.name: SUMIFS
math/sumifs.shortSummary: Adds values that satisfy multiple criteria.

math/sumproduct.name: SUMPRODUCT
math/sumproduct.shortSummary: Multiplies aligned values across arrays and returns the sum of those products.

math/sumsq.name: SUMSQ
math/sumsq.shortSummary: Returns the sum of squares of supplied numbers.

math/tan.name: TAN
math/tan.shortSummary: Returns the tangent of an angle in radians.

math/tanh.name: TANH
math/tanh.shortSummary: Returns the hyperbolic tangent of a number.

math/trunc.name: TRUNC
math/trunc.shortSummary: Truncates a number toward zero, optionally at a specified digit position.

random/rand.name: RAND
random/rand.shortSummary: Returns a uniformly distributed pseudo-random number in the interval `[0, 1)`.

random/randbetween.name: RANDBETWEEN
random/randbetween.shortSummary: Returns a random integer between two inclusive bounds.

reference-fns/index-fn.name: INDEX
reference-fns/index-fn.shortSummary: Returns the value or reference at a 1-based row and column within an array or range.
reference-fns/index-fn.signature: INDEX(arg1: any@range, arg2: number@scalar, arg3?: number@scalar)

reference-fns/indirect.name: INDIRECT
reference-fns/indirect.shortSummary: Converts text into a reference and returns the referenced value or range.

reference-fns/offset.name: OFFSET
reference-fns/offset.shortSummary: Returns a reference shifted from a starting reference by rows and columns.
reference-fns/offset.signature: OFFSET(arg1: range@range, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar, arg4?: number@scalar, arg5?: number@scalar)

stats/avedev.name: AVEDEV
stats/avedev.shortSummary: Returns the average of absolute deviations from the mean.

stats/beta-dist.name: BETA.DIST
stats/beta-dist.shortSummary: Returns the beta-distribution probability for `x`, with optional lower/upper bounds.
stats/beta-dist.signature: BETA.DIST(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar, arg4: number@scalar, arg5: number@scalar, arg6...: number@scalar)

stats/binom-dist.name: BINOM.DIST
stats/binom-dist.shortSummary: Returns the binomial probability for a count of successes across independent trials.
stats/binom-dist.signature: BINOM.DIST(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar, arg4: number@scalar)

stats/chisq-dist.name: CHISQ.DIST
stats/chisq-dist.shortSummary: Returns the chi-square probability for `x` with the specified degrees of freedom.
stats/chisq-dist.signature: CHISQ.DIST(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar)

stats/chisq-inv.name: CHISQ.INV
stats/chisq-inv.shortSummary: Returns the chi-square value whose left-tail probability is `probability`.

stats/chisq-test.name: CHISQ.TEST
stats/chisq-test.shortSummary: Returns the right-tail p-value from a chi-square goodness-of-fit style comparison.

stats/confidence-norm.name: CONFIDENCE.NORM
stats/confidence-norm.shortSummary: Returns the half-width of a confidence interval using a normal critical value.
stats/confidence-norm.signature: CONFIDENCE.NORM(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar)

stats/confidence-t.name: CONFIDENCE.T
stats/confidence-t.shortSummary: Returns the half-width of a confidence interval using a t critical value.
stats/confidence-t.signature: CONFIDENCE.T(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar)

stats/correl.name: CORREL
stats/correl.shortSummary: Returns the Pearson correlation coefficient between two numeric arrays.

stats/covariance-p.name: COVARIANCE.P
stats/covariance-p.shortSummary: Returns population covariance for two paired numeric data sets.

stats/covariance-s.name: COVARIANCE.S
stats/covariance-s.shortSummary: Returns sample covariance for two paired numeric data sets.

stats/devsq.name: DEVSQ
stats/devsq.shortSummary: Returns the sum of squared deviations from the mean.

stats/expon-dist.name: EXPON.DIST
stats/expon-dist.shortSummary: Returns the exponential-distribution probability at `x` for rate `lambda`.
stats/expon-dist.signature: EXPON.DIST(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar)

stats/f-dist.name: F.DIST
stats/f-dist.shortSummary: Returns the F-distribution probability for `x` with numerator and denominator degrees of freedom.
stats/f-dist.signature: F.DIST(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar, arg4: number@scalar)

stats/f-inv.name: F.INV
stats/f-inv.shortSummary: Returns the F value whose left-tail probability equals `probability`.
stats/f-inv.signature: F.INV(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar)

stats/f-test.name: F.TEST
stats/f-test.shortSummary: Returns the two-tailed p-value from an F-test comparing sample variances.

stats/fisher.name: FISHER
stats/fisher.shortSummary: Returns the Fisher z-transformation of a correlation-like value `x`.

stats/fisherinv.name: FISHERINV
stats/fisherinv.shortSummary: Returns the inverse Fisher transformation of `y`.

stats/forecast-linear.name: FORECAST.LINEAR
stats/forecast-linear.shortSummary: Returns a predicted y-value at `x` from simple linear regression over known data.

stats/frequency.name: FREQUENCY
stats/frequency.shortSummary: Returns a vertical frequency distribution for numeric data across bin cutoffs.

stats/gamma-dist.name: GAMMA.DIST
stats/gamma-dist.shortSummary: Returns the gamma-distribution probability at `x` for shape `alpha` and scale `beta`.
stats/gamma-dist.signature: GAMMA.DIST(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar, arg4: number@scalar)

stats/gauss.name: GAUSS
stats/gauss.shortSummary: Returns the standard normal area between `0` and `z`.

stats/geomean.name: GEOMEAN
stats/geomean.shortSummary: Returns the geometric mean of positive numeric values.

stats/growth.name: GROWTH
stats/growth.shortSummary: Returns fitted values from an exponential trend model.

stats/harmean.name: HARMEAN
stats/harmean.shortSummary: Returns the harmonic mean of positive numeric values.

stats/hypgeom-dist.name: HYPGEOM.DIST
stats/hypgeom-dist.shortSummary: Returns hypergeometric probabilities for successes drawn without replacement.
stats/hypgeom-dist.signature: HYPGEOM.DIST(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar, arg4: number@scalar, arg5: number@scalar)

stats/intercept.name: INTERCEPT
stats/intercept.shortSummary: Returns the y-intercept of the linear regression line for paired data.

stats/kurt.name: KURT
stats/kurt.shortSummary: Returns the sample excess kurtosis of a numeric distribution.

stats/large.name: LARGE
stats/large.shortSummary: Returns the k-th largest value in a data set.

stats/linest.name: LINEST
stats/linest.shortSummary: Returns linear-regression coefficients and optional fit statistics.

stats/logest.name: LOGEST
stats/logest.shortSummary: Returns parameters for an exponential model fitted to known data.

stats/lognorm-dist.name: LOGNORM.DIST
stats/lognorm-dist.shortSummary: Returns the log-normal probability at `x` as either a cumulative value or density.
stats/lognorm-dist.signature: LOGNORM.DIST(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar, arg4: number@scalar)

stats/lognorm-inv.name: LOGNORM.INV
stats/lognorm-inv.shortSummary: Returns the positive value `x` whose log-normal cumulative probability is `probability`.
stats/lognorm-inv.signature: LOGNORM.INV(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar)

stats/maxifs.name: MAXIFS
stats/maxifs.shortSummary: Returns the maximum numeric value in a range that meets all criteria.

stats/median.name: MEDIAN
stats/median.shortSummary: Returns the middle value of a numeric data set.

stats/minifs.name: MINIFS
stats/minifs.shortSummary: Returns the minimum numeric value in a range that meets all criteria.

stats/mode-mult.name: MODE.MULT
stats/mode-mult.shortSummary: Returns all modal values as a vertical array.

stats/mode-sngl.name: MODE.SNGL
stats/mode-sngl.shortSummary: Returns the most frequently occurring value in a data set.

stats/negbinom-dist.name: NEGBINOM.DIST
stats/negbinom-dist.shortSummary: Returns negative-binomial probabilities for failures observed before a target success count.
stats/negbinom-dist.signature: NEGBINOM.DIST(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar, arg4: number@scalar)

stats/norm-dist.name: NORM.DIST
stats/norm-dist.shortSummary: Returns the normal-distribution probability at `x` for a given mean and standard deviation.
stats/norm-dist.signature: NORM.DIST(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar, arg4: number@scalar)

stats/norm-inv.name: NORM.INV
stats/norm-inv.shortSummary: Returns the value `x` whose normal cumulative probability equals `probability`.
stats/norm-inv.signature: NORM.INV(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar)

stats/norm-s-dist.name: NORM.S.DIST
stats/norm-s-dist.shortSummary: Returns the standard normal probability for a z-score as either a CDF or PDF value.

stats/norm-s-inv.name: NORM.S.INV
stats/norm-s-inv.shortSummary: Returns the z-score whose standard normal cumulative probability matches `probability`.

stats/pearson.name: PEARSON
stats/pearson.shortSummary: Returns the Pearson correlation coefficient between two paired numeric arrays.

stats/percentile-exc.name: PERCENTILE.EXC
stats/percentile-exc.shortSummary: Returns the k-th percentile of a data set using exclusive interpolation.

stats/percentile-inc.name: PERCENTILE.INC
stats/percentile-inc.shortSummary: Returns the k-th percentile of a data set using inclusive interpolation.

stats/percentrank-exc.name: PERCENTRANK.EXC
stats/percentrank-exc.shortSummary: Returns the exclusive percentile rank of `x` within a numeric data array.

stats/percentrank-inc.name: PERCENTRANK.INC
stats/percentrank-inc.shortSummary: Returns the inclusive percentile rank of `x` within a numeric data array.

stats/phi.name: PHI
stats/phi.shortSummary: Returns the standard normal probability density at `x`.

stats/poisson-dist.name: POISSON.DIST
stats/poisson-dist.shortSummary: Returns the Poisson probability for event count `x` at average rate `mean`.
stats/poisson-dist.signature: POISSON.DIST(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar)

stats/product.name: PRODUCT
stats/product.shortSummary: Multiplies all numeric arguments and returns their product.

stats/quartile-exc.name: QUARTILE.EXC
stats/quartile-exc.shortSummary: Returns an exclusive quartile value for a data set.

stats/quartile-inc.name: QUARTILE.INC
stats/quartile-inc.shortSummary: Returns an inclusive quartile value for a data set.

stats/rank-avg.name: RANK.AVG
stats/rank-avg.shortSummary: Returns the rank position of a number, averaging the rank positions for ties.

stats/rank-eq.name: RANK.EQ
stats/rank-eq.shortSummary: Returns the rank position of a number within a data set, with ties sharing the same rank.

stats/rsq.name: RSQ
stats/rsq.shortSummary: Returns the coefficient of determination (`R^2`) for paired x/y data.

stats/skew.name: SKEW
stats/skew.shortSummary: Returns the sample skewness of a numeric distribution.

stats/slope.name: SLOPE
stats/slope.shortSummary: Returns the slope of the linear regression line for paired data.

stats/small.name: SMALL
stats/small.shortSummary: Returns the k-th smallest value in a data set.

stats/standardize.name: STANDARDIZE
stats/standardize.shortSummary: Returns the z-score of `x` relative to a mean and standard deviation.
stats/standardize.signature: STANDARDIZE(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar)

stats/stdev-p.name: STDEV.P
stats/stdev-p.shortSummary: Returns population standard deviation using `n` in the denominator.

stats/stdev-s.name: STDEV.S
stats/stdev-s.shortSummary: Estimates sample standard deviation using `n-1` in the denominator.

stats/steyx.name: STEYX
stats/steyx.shortSummary: Returns the standard error of y-estimates from a simple linear regression.

stats/t-dist.name: T.DIST
stats/t-dist.shortSummary: Returns the Student's t probability for `x` and a given degrees-of-freedom value.
stats/t-dist.signature: T.DIST(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar)

stats/t-dist-2t.name: T.DIST.2T
stats/t-dist-2t.shortSummary: Returns the two-tailed Student's t probability beyond `x`.

stats/t-inv.name: T.INV
stats/t-inv.shortSummary: Returns the t-value whose left-tail probability equals `probability`.

stats/t-inv-2t.name: T.INV.2T
stats/t-inv-2t.shortSummary: Returns the positive t critical value for a two-tailed probability.

stats/t-test.name: T.TEST
stats/t-test.shortSummary: Returns the p-value from a Student t-test comparing two numeric samples.
stats/t-test.signature: T.TEST(arg1: number@range, arg2: number@range, arg3: number@scalar, arg4: number@scalar)

stats/trend.name: TREND
stats/trend.shortSummary: Returns fitted y-values along a linear trend derived from known data.

stats/trimmean.name: TRIMMEAN
stats/trimmean.shortSummary: Returns the mean after trimming a percentage of values from both tails.

stats/var-p.name: VAR.P
stats/var-p.shortSummary: Returns population variance using `n` in the denominator.

stats/var-s.name: VAR.S
stats/var-s.shortSummary: Estimates sample variance using `n-1` in the denominator.

stats/weibull-dist.name: WEIBULL.DIST
stats/weibull-dist.shortSummary: Returns the Weibull-distribution probability at `x` for shape `alpha` and scale `beta`.
stats/weibull-dist.signature: WEIBULL.DIST(arg1: number@scalar, arg2: number@scalar, arg3: number@scalar, arg4: number@scalar)

stats/z-test.name: Z.TEST
stats/z-test.shortSummary: Returns the one-tailed p-value of a z-test against hypothesized mean `x`.
stats/z-test.signature: Z.TEST(arg1: number@range, arg2: number@scalar, arg3...: number@scalar)

text/arraytotext.name: ARRAYTOTEXT
text/arraytotext.shortSummary: Converts an array or range into a text representation.

text/char.name: CHAR
text/char.shortSummary: Returns the character specified by a number Excel uses Windows-1252 encoding for codes 1-255.

text/clean.name: CLEAN
text/clean.shortSummary: Removes non-printable ASCII control characters from text.

text/code.name: CODE
text/code.shortSummary: Returns a numeric code for the first character in a text string.

text/concat.name: CONCAT
text/concat.shortSummary: Concatenates multiple values into one text string.

text/concatenate.name: CONCATENATE
text/concatenate.shortSummary: Legacy alias for `CONCAT` that joins multiple values as text.

text/dollar.name: DOLLAR
text/dollar.shortSummary: Formats a number as currency text.

text/exact.name: EXACT
text/exact.shortSummary: Compares two text values for exact equality.

text/find.name: FIND
text/find.shortSummary: Returns the 1-based position of one text string inside another.

text/fixed.name: FIXED
text/fixed.shortSummary: Formats a number as text with fixed decimal places.
text/fixed.signature: FIXED(arg1: number@scalar, arg2?: number@scalar, arg3?: logical@scalar)

text/left.name: LEFT
text/left.shortSummary: Returns the leftmost characters from a text value.

text/len.name: LEN
text/len.shortSummary: Returns the number of characters in a text value.

text/mid.name: MID
text/mid.shortSummary: Returns a substring starting at a 1-based position.

text/proper.name: PROPER
text/proper.shortSummary: Capitalizes the first letter of each alphanumeric word.

text/replace.name: REPLACE
text/replace.shortSummary: Replaces part of a text string by position.

text/rept.name: REPT
text/rept.shortSummary: Repeats text a given number of times.

text/right.name: RIGHT
text/right.shortSummary: Returns the rightmost characters from a text value.

text/search.name: SEARCH
text/search.shortSummary: Returns the 1-based position of one text string inside another.

text/substitute.name: SUBSTITUTE
text/substitute.shortSummary: Replaces matching text within a string.

text/text.name: TEXT
text/text.shortSummary: Formats a value as text using a format pattern.

text/textafter.name: TEXTAFTER
text/textafter.shortSummary: Returns text that appears after a delimiter.
text/textafter.signature: TEXTAFTER(arg1: any@scalar, arg2: any@scalar, arg3?: number@scalar)

text/textbefore.name: TEXTBEFORE
text/textbefore.shortSummary: Returns text that appears before a delimiter.
text/textbefore.signature: TEXTBEFORE(arg1: any@scalar, arg2: any@scalar, arg3?: number@scalar)

text/textjoin.name: TEXTJOIN
text/textjoin.shortSummary: Joins text values using a delimiter, with optional empty-value filtering.

text/textsplit.name: TEXTSPLIT
text/textsplit.shortSummary: Splits text into a dynamic 2D array by column and optional row delimiters.
text/textsplit.signature: TEXTSPLIT(arg1: any@scalar, arg2: any@scalar, arg3?: any@scalar, arg4?: logical@scalar, arg5?: number@scalar, arg6?: any@scalar)

text/trim.name: TRIM
text/trim.shortSummary: Removes leading/trailing whitespace and collapses internal runs to single spaces.

text/unichar.name: UNICHAR
text/unichar.shortSummary: Returns the Unicode character for a given code point.

text/unicode.name: UNICODE
text/unicode.shortSummary: Returns the Unicode code point of the first character in text.

text/value.name: VALUE
text/value.shortSummary: Converts text that represents a number into a numeric value.

text/valuetotext.name: VALUETOTEXT
text/valuetotext.shortSummary: Converts a value to text representation.
